job_description:
Civil Engineer

First Capital Engineering, Inc., a successful multi-disciplinary firm with excellent client relationships, seeks an energetic civil engineer. Our staff is the key to our success. This individual shall team with other in-house professionals to offer superior services while working in an enjoyable environment. Positions not only have opportunities for advancement but have the opportunity to be mentored by various Registered Professionals.

Qualifications:

 * Bachelor degree in Civil Engineering, Master Degree a plus;
 * Possesses Engineer-In-Training (EIT) Certification;
 * Minimum 3-5 years of experience in related site/civil land development engineering;
 * General knowledge of local, county and Pennsylvania state land use processes and regulations;
 * Proficient in site, stormwater management, storm conveyance, grading, earthwork calculations, utility design and erosion and sediment control design;
 * Proficient in hydraulic and hydrological calculations to support land development design projects;
 * Experience with stormwater design and permitting processes including NPDES requirements;
 * Occasionally support other discipline projects including roadway improvement design, environmental, geotechnical, municipal review.
 * Active participation in local professional organizations a plus;
 * Demonstrated Autocad and Civil 3D skills with the ability to design land development plans from concept through completion;
 * Occasional field assignments to support land development projects;
 * Strong attention to detail with excellent analytical and judgment capabilities;
 * Ability to work independently, as well as, in a team environment.

Applicants must be able to pass a background check and drug test.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: From $70,000.00 per year

Benefits:

 * 401(k)
 * 401(k) matching
 * Dental insurance
 * Health insurance
 * Life insurance
 * Paid time off
 * Vision insurance

Schedule:

 * 8 hour shift

Education:

 * Bachelor's (Required)

Experience:

 * AutoCAD: 3 years (Required)

License/Certification:

 * Fundamentals of Engineering (Required)

Work Location: In person

Solli Engineering is seeking a Senior Project Manager with 10+ years experience in Civil Engineering to join our growing team in Monroe, CT. A successful candidate will be responsible for managing a team and contributing to the growth of an up and coming firm. Responsibilities will include the management of planning, design, permitting, preparation of specifications, septic design, stormwater calculations, and technical reports for a variety of land development projects. You will be able to see projects from initial concept through completion. Requirements:

 * Proven track record of successful Connecticut land development experience
 * Bachelors degree in Civil Engineering;
 * Possess a valid Connecticut Professional Engineer License;
 * 10+ years of experience in related site/civil land development engineering projects;
 * Knowledge of the Connecticut land use entitlement processes and local and state regulations;
 * Possess local experience with private developments performing site due diligence, preparing land use permits, understanding of zoning laws and presenting to municipal agencies;
 * Strong client development and client management abilities with ability to function as a seller / doer:
 * Respected, well-known and well-connected in the local marketplace;
 * Effectively manage projects from concept through construction documents;
 * Self-starter with the ability to manage, motivate, mentor and lead others;
 * Excellent communication skills, written and verbal;
 * Strong attention to detail with excellent analytical and judgment capabilities;
 * Ability to effectively manage a team;
 * Working knowledge of AutoCAD or Civil 3D, and Microsoft Office Suite applications;
 * Expertise in hydrologic/hydraulic analysis design including SWPPP preparation and water quality compliance;
 * Experienced in report and proposal writing including sub-contractor cost estimation;
 * Reliable transportation to access job sites and a valid drivers license in good standing;
 * Position requires work Monday through Friday with occasional evenings and weekends;

Solli Engineering is a land development consulting firm providing Site/Civil, Traffic and Transportation Engineering, Landscape Architecture and Surveying services to clients throughout the northeast. Projects range from residential, retail, commercial, industrial and mining. Currently working on projects in Connecticut, Massachusetts, New York, and New Hampshire, Solli Engineering has tremendous growth opportunities, and is looking for a valuable team member to help us continue to excel in the industry. Equal Opportunity Employer

Job Type: Full-time

Benefits:

 * 401(k)
 * 401(k) matching
 * Dental insurance
 * Health insurance
 * Paid time off
 * Referral program
 * Vision insurance

Experience:

 * land development: 10 years (Required)

Education:

 * Bachelor's (Required)

License:

 * Professional Engineer (Required)

Work Location: In person

